			<div class="content" id="post-content-1784685">
									

<p>I have no idea how to organize this post, so I'm gonna use bullets to list my thoughts.</p>
<ul>
<li>I saw it at -14. If you want to blame anyone for it not being here any more, blame the readers.</li>
<li>The original version of this was created in late 2011 &#8212; it was just <em>written</em> in the old style. It's no more &quot;one of our last links to the past&quot; than any of the various ancient SCPs that managed to get by on <em>being well-written</em>.</li>
<li>You want something in the style of the old 935 on the wiki, do one of these things:
<ul>
<li>Write one yourself</li>
<li>Make a convincing argument that other people should attempt to do so, because it is NOT too late to use the old canon.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>If you were really invested in the last version, it was dropping in rating for a while and Roget asked to do a rewrite two weeks ago. You could have offered to help him on it, or gotten in before him and just done it yourself.</li>
</ul>
<p>For reference: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-400940">http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-400940</a> (I have no idea how long this link will last)</p>
<p>But most importantly: getting <em>angry</em> at someone who wanted to make an article acceptable to the wiki is rude. Especially when, if you'd gotten your way (and kept it the same), it would not be on the wiki AT ALL. So express your distaste for the present version, make your suggestions, and chillax.</p>

